parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the fuel system can cause the engine to falter, stall, or catch fire, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: especially during left turns or hard acceleration
fire starting in the rear of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the gear shift lever can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The gear shift lever breaks off
the gear shift lever feels loose or wobbly
the gear shift lever is difficult to move
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the speedometer head can cause the driver to be unaware of their speed, leading to accidents or traffic violations.
symptoms: The speedometer needle is stuck or faulty
the speedometer display is blank or faulty
the speedometer is not functioning at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine cooling system can cause engine overheating, leading to engine damage, breakdowns, and potentially even engine failure, which can result in costly repairs and pose a safety risk to the driver and passengers.
Oil leaks can cause engine damage, leading to premature wear and tear, and potentially even engine failure, which can result in costly repairs and pose a safety risk to the driver and passengers.
The failure of the heater core can cause coolant leakage, which can lead to engine overheating, damage, and potentially cause a loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: sweet or burning smell inside the vehicle
visible signs of coolant leakage under the hood.
